  "body": "### Issue description\r\n\r\nI am running a test script using mainnet fork, and using alchemy as per instructions. However, I am getting inconsistent behaviour when running the same script multiple times. Given that it is pinned to a specific blockNumber, I can't see a reason for this happening. The failures happen when calling functions on the [mUSD contract](https://etherscan.io/address/0xe2f2a5C287993345a840Db3B0845fbC70f5935a5) which has a number of external dependencies (lending platforms etc).\r\n\r\nAdditional info: time has been increased 1 week.\r\n\r\n**The error happens around 30% of the time and I cannot pin down any particular reproduction issues.. so just bringing this to the developers attention, not expecting a fix.**\r\n\r\n#### Config\r\n\r\n```\r\nrequire(\"hardhat-gas-reporter\");\r\nrequire(\"@nomiclabs/hardhat-waffle\");\r\nrequire(\"@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers\");\r\nrequire(\"@tenderly/hardhat-tenderly\");\r\nrequire(\"hardhat-typechain\");\r\n\r\nrequire(\"ts-node/register\");\r\n\r\n...\r\n\r\n  hardhat: {\r\n    forking: {\r\n      url:\r\n        \"https://eth-mainnet.alchemyapi.io/v2/xxx\",\r\n      blockNumber: 11451451,\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Error\r\n\r\n```\r\nError: Transaction reverted without a reason\r\n    at <UnrecognizedContract>.<unknown> (0x0...)\r\n    at <UnrecognizedContract>.<unknown> (0x0...)\r\n    at runMicrotasks (<anonymous>)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:97:5)\r\n    at EthModule._sendTransactionAndReturnHash (.../hardhat-network/provider/modules/eth.ts:1303:9)\r\n    at HardhatNetworkProvider.request (.../hardhat-network/provider/provider.ts:102:18)\r\n    at EthersProviderWrapper.send\r\n    ```",
